GEMATRIAFBC(1)              General Commands Manual             GEMATRIAFBC(1)

NAME
       gematriafbc — a simple gematria calculator - console version

SYNOPSIS
       gematriafbc [OPTIONS] [WORD,PHRASE,VALUE] [FILENAME]

DESCRIPTION
       Enter a word or phrase to find the gematria.  Enter !q to quit or !c to
       clear the screen.  The maximum allowable entry depends on your  console
       size,  with an absolute maximum entry of 127 characters. Use the up and
       down arrow keys to scroll through previous entries.   Previous  entries
       are  saved  in a file in the user's home folder.  ESC clears the entry.
       The program can also build databases and match words or phrases without
       running normally.

OPTIONS
       -b [filename], --build [filename]
              Build a database from file.  Outputs to file.

       -h, --help
              Report the command  options and exit.

       -l, --log
              Log  the  session  (to  file  in  current  directory as Gematri‐
              aFBC.log).

       -m [word] [filename], --match [word] [filename]
              Match a word, phrase or value to a database.  Outputs to file.

       -r, --reverse
              Append reversed forms to output.

       -v, --version
              Report version and exit.

       -V, --verbose
              Verbose output.

       -w, --warranty
              Report warranty and license conditions then exit.

FILES
       HOME/.GematriaFBC_hist

       CURRENT/GematriaFBC.log

